	<h1 class="w3-teal">CSS: cascading style sheets</h1>
	
	<pre>
CSS is for cascading style sheets. 

CSS has the syntax of 

	element {property:value, property:value}

CSS Box Model

	border property is the border around the element

		p {border:1px solid red}

	margin is the space outside border

	padding is the space inside border

CSS: selecting element by id has the syntax of

	element#id{property:value, property:value}

CSS: selecting element by class has the syntax of

	element.id{property:value, property:value}

CSS for links

	a:link {color:green}
	a:visited {color:green}
	a:hover {color:green}
	a:active {color:green}

	text-decoration:none/underline/...

CSS for tables

	border
	border-collapse
	padding
	border-spacing

CSS for lists

	list-style-type
	display:inline(horizontally)



	
	
